The '''Kingdom of Varlamore''', also known as the '''Shining Kingdom''', is a [[kingdom]] found in the continent of [[Zeah]], found far west of the mainland across the [[Western Sea]]. It is one of the three regions that make up the continent, the other two being the Kingdom of [[Great Kourend]] and the [[Kebos Lowlands]]{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ed|url=https://twitter.com/JagexEd/status/1082677172962246657|date=8 January 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/N1ZuU|archivedate=29 May 2020|quote=[The Kebos Lowlands are] a separate region to Great Kourend and one of the three regions that make up the continent.}}.

The people of Varlamore, ruled by [[Queen Zyanyi Arkan]],{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|quote=Zyanyi Arkan, the Sun Queen. She's the ruler of Varlamore, the kingdom in the south.}} are known to worship [[Ralos]], the god of the sun.{{CiteNPC|npc=Brother Aimeri|quote=I am a travelling monk from the distant land of Varlamore... I worship Ralos, a common practice where I am from.}}

While players cannot currently visit the kingdom, there are four known areas of the kingdom:
*[[Avium Savannah]]
*[[Civitas illa Fortis]], the capital of the kingdom.
*[[Proudspire]]
*[[Tempestus]]

==History==
The Kingdom was formed by refugees fleeing from [[Great Kourend]] during the Age of Strife 1,030 years ago, when [[Xeric]] ruled the kingdom.{{CiteText|text=Imafore's betrayal|quote=The Kingdom of Varlamore was formed in a very similar way to Kourend, by those fleeing the Age of Strife.}} Since their founding, they managed to avoid war with Great Kourend for nearly 1,000 years.{{CiteText|text=Imafore's betrayal|quote=Varlamore managed to avoid conflict for nearly a thousand years and in that time it became one of the most prosperous kingdoms in the world.}}

However, after Emperor Imafore killed the Kourend royal family during a grand feast celebrating his 30th birthday party by poisoning their drinks,{{CiteText|text=Imafore's betrayal|quote=He had the servants open a barrel of his finest Aldarin red. Then, he made a toast, to the royal family of Kourend... The entire royal family collapsed before the emperor who looked on with a smile on his face.}} the kingdom declared war on Varlamore,{{CiteText|text=Imafore's betrayal|quote=...one of the more interesting conflicts is the most recent one, the war with Varlamore.}} with the Emperor killed in battle. The reason for poisoning the Kourend royal family remains unknown, as Imafore took the secret to his grave.{{CiteText|text=Imafore's betrayal|quote=To this day, no one knows exactly why Imafore murdered them. It's a secret he took to his grave...}}

The war had ended sometime before or during the reign of [[Great Kourend]]'s King Kharedst III in the 132nd to 134th decade. In the hope of repairing the relationship with Varlamore, which had been destroyed after the war, the King ordered an envoy be sent to Varlamore to transport the [[Royal Accord of Twill]], a document of great historical importance to Great Kourend, to be displayed in the Grand Museum of [[Civitas illa Fortis]],{{CiteText|text=Varlamore envoy|quote=Despite the protests of many, the King insisted that the Accord be taken with the envoy to Varlamore to be displayed in the Grand Museum of Civitas illa Fortis.}} Varlamore's capital. However, the Accord became lost at sea,{{CiteText|text=Varlamore envoy|quote=The ship was travelling off the south coast of Kourend, when it was caught up in a great storm. The ship, the crew and the Accord itself were all lost beneath the waves.}} and remained so until it was recovered by [[Artur Hosidius]] in the 141st decade.

Today, the betrayal of Emperor Imafore remains fresh in the minds of Kourend's people, and the trust has yet to be regained,{{CiteText|text=Varlamore envoy|quote=...the war with Varlamore remains fresh in the minds of Kourend's people. The betrayal of Emperor Imafore is hard to forget and it is likely this mistrust will continue for numerous lifetimes.}} although it appears that [[Queen Zyanyi Arkan]] is eager to ease tensions between the two kingdoms during her visit to [[Great Kourend]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Queen Zyanyi Arkan|quote=From today, the sun will shine on our two kingdoms once more. The mistakes of the past are now behind us.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Commander Fullore|quote=[The King is] keen to put an end to the animosity between the two kingdoms. Rumor has it [Queen Zyanyi Arkan] feels the same way.}}
